<p>?Wildfire frequency and intensity is projected to increase which means that higher leaf flammability in sheltered forest species has the potential to exacerbate the effects of changing weather conditions to place sheltered forest habitat, their plants and their animals, at even higher risk of catastrophic wildfire,? Dr Murray says.</p>
<p>?If the gullies are becoming more at risk of going up in huge fires, then where will the animals go?? he says.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-summary field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">In summary:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><ul><li>Scientists have found that plant communities in gullies, where animals typically take shelter during bushfires, are potentially more flammable than exposed woodlands</li>
<li>With frequent, more intense bushfires predicted for south-eastern Australia, it's feared these biodiverse wildlife refuges are now at risk</li>
</ul></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-partners field-type-link-field field-label-above"><div class="field-label">This research is funded by:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><a href="https://www.education.gov.au/research-training-program">Australian Government Research Training Program</a></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-themes field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><a href="/themes/health-and-science">Health and Science</a></div><div class="field-item odd"><a href="/themes/social-justice-and-sustainability">Social Justice and Sustainability</a></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-source field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">The Newsroom</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-new-byline field-type-link-field field-label-above"><div class="field-label">Byline:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><a href="https://www.uts.edu.au/staff/marea.martlew">Marea Martlew</a></div></div></div>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1519094765;}}s:7:"channel";a:4:{s:5:"title";s:49:"UTS News Room - Social Justice and Sustainability";s:4:"link";s:67:"http://newsroom.uts.edu.au/themes/social-justice-and-sustainability";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:7:"tagline";N;}s:9:"textinput";a:0:{}s:5:"image";a:0:{}s:9:"feed_type";s:3:"RSS";s:12:"feed_version";s:3:"2.0";s:8:"encoding";s:10:"ISO-8859-1";s:16:"_source_encoding";s:0:"";s:5:"ERROR";s:0:"";s:7:"WARNING";s:0:"";s:19:"_CONTENT_CONSTRUCTS";a:6:{i:0;s:7:"content";i:1;s:7:"summary";i:2;s:4:"info";i:3;s:5:"title";i:4;s:7:"tagline";i:5;s:9:"copyright";}s:16:"_KNOWN_ENCODINGS";a:3:{i:0;s:5:"UTF-8";i:1;s:8:"US-ASCII";i:2;s:10:"ISO-8859-1";}s:5:"stack";a:0:{}s:9:"inchannel";b:0;s:6:"initem";b:0;s:9:"incontent";b:0;s:11:"intextinput";b:0;s:7:"inimage";b:0;s:17:"current_namespace";b:0;s:15:"sourc